# Git safety

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, `outputs/`, `wandb/`, or large data under `data/raw/`.
- Do not run destructive git commands (`push --force`, `reset --hard`) unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do not create commits unless the user requests them.
- In `autonomous` mode, still do not auto-commit; log intent in `research/decision_log.md`.
